<doc id="1006463" wikidata="Q2273879" url="?curid=1006463" title="Serpentine River (New Zealand)">
<text>The Serpentine River is a minor river on the north western flanks of the Richmond Range in the South Island of New Zealand.

It passes through a plantation forest near the town of Richmond before joining the Roding River, eventually emptying into Tasman Bay.

